text: Cypress is an unincorporated community in Harris County, Texas, United States. It is also a suburb of Houston, Texas. As of 2020, the population was at 184,851 people. It includes neighborhoods such as Coles Crossing, and has schools such as Farney Elementary, Goodson Middle School, Spillane Middle School, and Cy-Woods High School. The main school district for this area is Cypress Fairbanks Independent School District. Category:Unincorporated communities in Texas Category:Settlements in Harris County, Texas
title: Cypress, Texas
